    "dek": "The cold, still afternoon when the price of keeping the lights on hit \u00a32,900 a megawatt-hour.",
    "body_md": "On a cold, calm January day the wind faded to a tenth of its capacity while demand stayed high. Britain leaned on its interconnectors for close to six gigawatts of imported power \u2014 around three-fifths of everything the cables can carry \u2014 and the system price spiked to \u00a32,900 a megawatt-hour, roughly forty times an ordinary afternoon. By the end of the day the bill for those imports came to \u00a387.5 million, the most Britain has ever paid to import electricity in a single day. Press play and watch the day tighten.",
